page.title: 13Housing on Horse-Eye & Area
page.content: There are 3 distinct types of housing on Horse-Eye Level. 9 working farm houses and 12 cottages on the marshland. 2 cottages are 18th century Listed Buildings. One has no special features but Cherrycroft has 2 storeys, 5 windows faced with grey headers with red brick dressings and quoins. Stringcourse of grey headers. Slate Roof. Doorway with heavy flat hood on brackets & door of 6 fielded panels placed up 2 semi-circular steps. This cottage has a Sussex Barn. Park Homes caravan site provides 112 residential caravans for retired people. A small section of a large council house estate infringes on to the area in direct contrast to the rural character. Gas is supplied to the council estate but not to the rural areas.
